13/08/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK plans to hand over its police stations to the Kosovo Police Service by next year, UN Police Commissioner Stefan Feller told reporters Thursday (12 August). Feller, whose mandate is expiring soon, said the transfer of operational tasks would be conducted this year and in 2005. He added that the training of Kosovo's specialised police units would require more time. 
In other news Thursday, the OSCE mission chief in Kosovo, Ambassador Pascal Fieschi, urged Kosovo Serbs to participate in the 23 October local elections. Fieschi reiterated the international community's disappointment with the decision by Serb parties to boycott the elections. (Tanjug - 13/08/04; B92 - 12/08/04) 
